1:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/femarr80492frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=145.topic>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://cofk.com/members/kogg.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Clerics and Non-Clerics...  Opinion please...</span><hr size=1> I am curious who you think needs a symbol...<br>
<br>
I often cast my symbol on whomever (in the group/guild) asks.  But its becoming very expensive...  Thank god I have a few people who will occasionally throw a few peridots my way...  1 Peridot costs me about 12 plat...  and I use one every time I cast Symbol of Naltron.   <br>
<br>
Its really difficult for me to say no, to someone who feels they need a symbol to survive.  When in fact an extra 300 hp would only allow them to live 2 seconds longer.<br>
<br>
IMO I think that the only people who really need symbols are the main assist/tank the puller (often the same person) and any casters (necro, chanter, mage in particular cause they have so few hit points to begin with).<br>
<br>
This is just an opinion poll...  And will hopefully make everyone aware of what it costs a cleric to try and keep you alive...  ie:  If you are rezzed by a kind cleric...  Give him/her 5 peridots...  I for one, know that I would prefer that to cash!<br>
<br>
Not that I ever accept money from a guildmate for doing a rez.<br>
<br>
<br>
Kog<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/ubraydinfirecaster.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Braydin Firecaster</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#993300>(2/23/02 3:12:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/femarr80492frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=145.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/braydinfirecaster/braydinicon.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Clerics and Non-Clerics...  Opinion please...</span><hr size=1> As a caster I dont feel i need Symbol... If I take that much damage, it means I am not playing like I should be and If I die, its alot cheaper to Rez me. Peridots do make a great donation, and when I am in a group with a cleric I always give them to the cleric when I loot them.... sometime it shocks them! Usually they thank me alot and sometime they will symbol me with the one that needs a jasper instead of a dot. That makes me happy enough right there, I got a buff in the window...doesn't matter what it is...it is there wooohooo <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Braydin Firecaster<BR>
