</TD></TR></TABLE></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/usilvarien.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Silvarien</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#993300>(2/23/02 12:10:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/femarr80492frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=145.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Clerics and Non-Clerics...  Opinion please...</span><hr size=1>     Symbol should only go to melee's and the chanter. I agree with Bray that if a caster is getting hit often then they're not playing right. I'm a ranger and i never get hit unless i want to (in a controlled group situation that is). If i can do it, you can do it. Enchanters have to constantly deal with hits here and there mezzing mobs, and in many cases if the ench dies you all die.  The biggest waste is when a cleric wastes 3 symbols on the group casters and they never get hit or die anyway. Just an opinion don't flame me.=p <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/bemarr80492.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=nerdlinger>Nerdlinger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#993300>(2/23/02 1:08:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/femarr80492frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=145.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Clerics and Non-Clerics...  Opinion please...</span><hr size=1> I like to get the PIN when possible if we are in a tough zone.  I never ask or expect to get the NAL.  If a group is low on melee I often end up doing some fighting when things get hairy.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/ukogginnstormkoffinn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kogginn Stormkoffinn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fearless Leader and Webmaster</span><br>  Posts: 140<br> <font color=#993300>(2/23/02 3:53:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/femarr80492frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=145.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://cofk.com/members/kogg.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Clerics and Non-Clerics...  Opinion please...</span><hr size=1> Ok...  Good input...  Now I want to add something...  Many times a mob will beat on a player even if that player has cast no spells or done no damage...  ie. you are sitting in the background medding or look at the mob the wrong way (some mobs just dont do what they are supposed to, lol)<br>
<br>
In a situation like this, where you (as the cleric) notice that player C is taking a lot of unprevoked damage...  Shouldnt he/she get a symbol?  I think so.<br>
<br>
I frequently use Pinzarm on the full group when in outdoors zones or less dangerous situations.  After all Jasper only cost about 12 GP a piece as opposed to 12pp for a Dot...<br>
<br>
I generally try to have a stock of 2+ stacks of Dots and 3 or 4 stacks of jaspers on me...  Its not hard to go through a stack of gems in one night...  And even more in a raid situation.<br>
<br>
See ya IG.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Kog <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/uazurewolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Azurewolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#993300>(2/23/02 4:06:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/femarr80492frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=145.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Clerics and Non-Clerics...  Opinion please...</span><hr size=1> I think most people will agree that using the higher buffs on the tanks and enchies is appropriate. After that, if there is mana and/or components available for the lower buffs for the rest of the group then that is great! I know, however, that I do not &quot;expect&quot; to get those buffs if I am not a tank or enchie in the group. If I get them, great...if not, then I am sure there is a reason (ie low on mana etc.)<br>
<br>
As far as the random unprovoked attack...well, in my mind that is just one of the fun risks of the game. If it happens to me, oh well. I would never expect a cleric to use up their expensive components keeping buffs on me just on the off chance that I may get a surprise aggro. But I also tend to be very laid back about dying...I mean, they are just pixels after all hehe. <br>
<br>
I do get annoyed by people that whine that they would not have died if they had been fully buffed or try to fault a group member for it. I think on the whole most clerics are gonna err on the side of over buffing. They have played this character for years for the whole purpose of saving people and I find it few and far between where a cleric is going to risk his group members. <br>
<br>
Well...my 2 cps there...seems more like 5pp maybe..got a little long winded there, hehe. Sorry folks..guess I need to lay off the coffee today!!!<br>
<br>
~Azurewolf <p>~Hearts are strongest when they beat in response to noble ideas~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/uozzmond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ozzmond</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#993300>(2/23/02 4:19:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/femarr80492frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=145.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Clerics and Non-Clerics...  Opinion please...</span><hr size=1> in theory,the main assist and the enchanter(if the chanter isnt getting hit,he's either good with spell timing or not doing too much),that's easier said than done,some instances(ranger with nice proc's will inadvertantly draw aggro away from the MA)also could stand for a symbol. <br>
<br>
In total agreement that if an offensive caster draws his own heat,he's doing it wrong.(personally the 50+ zones hit so damn hard,for me it's all about avoiding aggro and doing my role period.<br>
Example:&quot;sorry Mr shaman,youre going to just have to slow the mob when it's at 85% health and not 95%,im not going to Tash any sooner).<br>
Personally if it were me playing cleric,it wld be peridot's for the MA and chanter/bard,and jasper for everyone else. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/uzoldarf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>zoldarf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Officer</span><br>  Posts: 122<br> <font color=#993300>(2/23/02 5:08:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/femarr80492frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=145.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.ffshrine.com/ff1/images/chaost.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Clerics and Non-Clerics...  Opinion please...</span><hr size=1> Main assist and chanter.  Cleric if things are rough.  It's not the gem costs per se, it's the mana.  Buffing everyone takes lots of mana, and generates unnecessary downtime.<br>
<br>
-Zoldarf <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/udalamarndarkgem.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dalamarn Darkgem</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#993300>(2/23/02 7:55:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/femarr80492frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=145.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Clerics and Non-Clerics...  Opinion please...</span><hr size=1> Peridots can get expensive.  Necros need a damage taking shield.  The reason I say this is we have near the lowest HPs of any in the game, and our lich spells are constantly draining us of life, so we need the buffer.  Many of our spells draw HUGE aggro. <br>
<br>
HOWEVER, we can cast our own shields.  As with yours, the lower one takes a jasper and the higher one takes a peridot.  This buff DAILY saves my ass and allows me to finish casting without being interrupted.  It's good for handling adds or sucking up an AE spell that would wipe out your low on life necro.  I'd say, throw a jasper symbol to your nec IF he doesn't have one of his own.  I wouldn't waste the peridot unless you were in one hellish place where the extra HPs would mean life or death. <p><a href="http://members.aol.com/wvvetteman/images/dalonhorse1.jpg" target="_blank">
<img src="http://members.aol.com/wvvetteman/images/dalonhorse1.jpg" border="0" WIDTH=108 HEIGHT=222>
</a> <BR> ~Dalamarn Darkgem~ <BR>~Harbinger of Death~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/ustyrowhatever.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Styrowhatever</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 74<br> <font color=#993300>(2/25/02 5:18:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/femarr80492frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=145.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://bindpoint.com/images/styrogur_tux_small.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Clerics and Non-Clerics...  Opinion please...</span><hr size=1> By default, I use peridots for puller/main assist and the enchie. If during the group I notice that anyone else ends up taking a lot of damage quickly (can anyone say &quot;necro?&quot;), I'll use a peridot on them to give me more time to slap a heal on them during a fight.<br>
<br>
If I find I'm getting aggroed a lot I'll give myself one.<br>
<br>
I'm also more likely to use a peridot on guild members in my group than non-guild members.<br>
<br>
 <p>Styrogur Dreadnaught (Ogre Warrior)<BR>Styrona Nightingale (High Elf Cleric)<BR>Styrogyro Mindwarper (Erudite Enchanter)<BR>Styrosham (Ogre Shaman)<BR>Styrog (Dwarf Rogue)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/ufaewin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faewin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#993300>(2/27/02 5:29:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/femarr80492frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=145.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Clerics and Non-Clerics...  Opinion please...</span><hr size=1> Already been said I know but...<br>
<br>
The Enchie neeeds SYMBOL!!!! :-)<br>
<br>
Hehe, as you say it only means a few more seconds alive, but those seconds really, REALLY count.<br>
<br>
I find lately that im constantly using Rune on myself in DL as I'm getting some really bad aggro, this has a similar effect but costs more as rune wears out and symbol doesnt.<br>
<br>
Also would it not be prudent to get a high CHA character, myself or Ozz and I'm sure there are more Chars here, to buy these in bulk for you and other clerics.  Peridots cost me about 10.5 pp I think.  Thats 30pp saved a stack, but I s'pose it depends on how many you use. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub65.ezboard.com/ustyrowhatever.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Styrowhatever</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 80<br> <font color=#993300>(2/27/02 8:02:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub65.ezboard.com/femarr80492frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=145.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://bindpoint.com/images/styrogur_tux_small.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Clerics and Non-Clerics...  Opinion please...</span><hr size=1> Yes, I usually have Styrogyro buy peridots for Styrona. Only cost 10.5 plat. <p><TABLE BORDER="5" CELLSPACING="5" CELLPADDING="3" BGCOLOR="#330066" BORDERCOLOR="#3300FF">
